headline: MongoDB Stock Gains After Naming Cloudflare Exec Next CEO, Publishing Early Q3 Results
summary: MongoDB stock rallied but then gave back some of those gains after announcing a new CEO and preliminary quarterly results.

headline: MongoDB taps Cloudflare executive Chirantan Desai as CEO
summary: Desai will succeed Dev Ittycheria, who is stepping down after more than 11 years leading the company.  Shares of MongoDB rose 5% following the announcement.  Desai, a veteran technology executive with over 25 years of experience, previously also held senior roles at ServiceNow, EMC, Symantec and Oracle.

headline: NWN Appoints Mike Qualley as Chief Operating Officer to Accelerate AI‑Powered Services Growth & Operational Excellence
summary: BOSTON, Mass., November 03, 2025--NWN, the leading provider of AI‑powered technology solutions, today announced the appointment of Mike Qualley as Chief Operating Officer (COO). Qualley will lead company‑wide operations with a mandate to drive Operational Excellence as the company scales NWN’s platform to support over 6000 clients across North America.
